text: Uno Kajak (born 9 May 1933) is an Estonian skier. He competed in the Nordic combined event at the 1956 Winter Olympics. Kajak graduated in 1948 from Rakvere Elementary School No. 2. In 1956 he graduated from Tartu State University (now the University of Tartu), having studied physical education. ==References== Category:1933 births Category:Living people Category:Estonian male Nordic combined skiers Category:Estonian male biathletes Category:Olympic Nordic combined skiers of the Soviet Union Category:Nordic combined skiers at the 1956 Winter Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Tartu Category:University of Tartu alumni
